[1]
Date: Mon, 18 Jul 2005
From: S K Sharif <sksharif@ikenya.com>

4 deaths after drinking fermented milk- Gucha District, Nyanza Province, Kenya
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4 children died and 39 were admitted to hospital in Gucha District in
Nyanza Province in Kenya on Sat 16 Jul 2005. All patients fell sick after
drinking colostrum which was fermented. Traditional culture in the area
dictates that after a cow gives birth, the colostrum is fermented and then
served to friends.
In this case, the colostrum was fermented for over 5 days. People who
consumed the fermented colostrum started developing symptoms of diarrhea
and vomiting within 6 hours. 4 children died within 6-10 hours of
consumption of the fermented colostrum. Others were admitted to the
district hospital. Most of the others are in a stable condition. A sample
of the milk has been sent to Nairobi and Kisumu since there are no
facilities to culture at the district hospital.
--
Dr S K Sharif
Ministry of Health, Kenya
