[2]
Date: Mon, 18 Jul 2005
From: Shamsudeen <oshamsudeen@hotmail.com>
Source: BBC News [edited]
<http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/pr/fr/-/1/hi/world/africa/4692949.stm>

Children die at Kenyan milk party
---------------------------------
4 children from a Kenyan family have died after drinking contaminated milk
during a traditional celebration. 39 other relatives went to hospital with
vomiting and diarrhea but are now said to be stable.
When a cow gives birth for the first time, the Abagusii community holds a
special party, Chiribiriria, in which the whole family drinks the cow's
milk. The milk is fermented over a week and it is thought it became
contaminated over this time.
The 8 year old daughter of the cow's owner was one of those who died, along
with 3 of her cousins, aged between 4 and 7. They all came from Bohtibigi
village in the western Gucha district.
Medical Officer of Health James Gisami warned that good hygiene must be
observed when preparing milk. "Milk is very delicate and can be a good
culture media for bacteria. It must be boiled and not warmed," he said.
--
O Shamsudeen
<oshamsudeen@hotmail.com>
